<distribution-code display="yes">II</distribution-code><congress>119th CONGRESS</congress><session>2d Session</session><legis-num>S. 4505</legis-num><current-chamber>IN THE SENATE OF THE UNITED STATES</current-chamber><action><action-date date="20260512">May 12, 2026</action-date><action-desc><sponsor name-id="S376">Ms. Ernst</sponsor> (for herself, <cosponsor name-id="S413">Mr. Padilla</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="S317">Mr. Barrasso</cosponsor>, and <cosponsor name-id="S330">Mr. Bennet</cosponsor>) introduced the following bill; which was read twice and referred to the <committee-name committee-id="SSGA00">Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs</committee-name></action-desc></action><legis-type>A BILL</legis-type><official-title>To require the United States Postal Service to designate ZIP Codes for certain communities.</official-title></form><legis-body style="OLC"><section id="idccf4e97329724094a510ef3c1930805d" section-type="section-one"><enum>1.</enum><header>Designation of ZIP Codes</header><text display-inline="no-display-inline">Not later than 1 year after the date of enactment of this Act, the United States Postal Service shall designate a single, unique ZIP Code for each of the following communities:</text><paragraph id="id09a69db975d04e33ad29d594ee2fd275"><enum>(1)</enum><text>Canyon Lake, California.</text></paragraph><paragraph id="ida3e676d62cd743c3b01d9fcb1334d20f"><enum>(2)</enum><text>Eastvale, California.</text></paragraph><paragraph id="ideb9b3d88b007406e9e44fd0679b86d03"><enum>(3)</enum><text>Hidden Hills, California.</text></paragraph><paragraph id="id24c7530f8e8e40dd867aaf22b2eab4c6"><enum>(4)</enum><text>Industry, California.</text></paragraph><paragraph commented="no" display-inline="no-display-inline" id="idf271a3a9a26e4327afcd12bdd2840fca"><enum>(5)</enum><text>Irwindale, California.</text></paragraph><paragraph id="id482ad215f01a43869f3a102051ec7c1e"><enum>(6)</enum><text>North Tustin, California.</text></paragraph><par